description: This is part of a sound kit i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled.. i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-kit_highhat03.wav
tags: cuts digital drum-kit fx glitch noise slices soundeffect
